# Documentation Structure

The documentation is organized in the `docs/` directory, with a hierarchical structure.

## Content Organization

- [docs/GeneralSettings/](mdc:docs/GeneralSettings): Contains general settings documentation
  - Basic setup guides
  - Firebase configuration
  - Notifications
  - App icon setup
  - Package name configuration
  - And more

## Adding New Documentation

1. Create a new markdown file in the appropriate directory with the `.md` extension
2. Add metadata at the top of the file:
   ```md
   ---
   sidebar_position: X
   title: Your Title
   ---
   ```
3. Use Markdown syntax for the content
4. Add the file to the sidebar by updating [sidebars.js](mdc:sidebars.js) if needed

## Markdown Features

- Use standard Markdown syntax
- Add images with `![alt text](mdc:img/image.png)`
- Create code blocks with triple backticks and specify the language
- Use admonitions for callouts:
  ```md
  :::note
  This is a note
  :::

  :::tip
  This is a tip
  :::

  :::warning
  This is a warning
  :::
  ```
